1. *Probamo* danas da završimo sve obaveze. (Let's try to finish all the tasks today.)
2. Nadam se da ćemo uspeti da *probamo* taj novi restoran. (I hope we will manage to try that new restaurant.)
3. Ako ne *probamo* da naučimo novi jezik, nećemo napredovati. (If we don't try to learn a new language, we won't progress.)
4. Da li si već *probao* ovaj novi sok? (Have you already tried this new juice?)
5. Ne bih da *probam* taj novi film, čuo sam da je loš. (I don't want to try that new movie, I heard it's bad.)
6. *Probajmo* još jednom da rešimo ovaj problem. (Let's try to solve this problem once again.)
7. Moramo *probati* nove ideje ako želimo da napredujemo. (We have to try new ideas if we want to progress.)
8. *Probavaš* li da mi nešto kažeš? (Are you trying to tell me something?)
9. Nismo uspeli da *probamo* novi recept jer nam nedostaju sastojci. (We couldn't try the new recipe because we're missing ingredients.)
10. Kako bismo *probali* taj novi hobi? (How can we try that new hobby?)

Note: In Serbian, the word "probamo" is a verb in the first person plural present tense, meaning "let's try". The other forms of the verb "probati" (to try) are also used in these sentences, such as "probamo" (let's try), "probam" (I try), "probajmo" (let's try), "probati" (to try), and "probavaš" (you're trying).